notes_display: Medal commemorates the successes of Eugene & Marlborough.  Medal composed of white metal with copper plug.  Edge enscription reads: ARMORVM FOEDERATORVM FRVCTVS (The fruits of the allied arms).
issue_obverse_figure_description_s: Bust of Prince Eugene on left, facing right, and bust of the Duke of Marlborough on right, facing left.
issue_obverse_legend_s: EVGENIVS . FRANC . DVX . SABAVD . * IOHANNES . DVX . D . MARLB . S . R . I . P . *
issue_reverse_figure_description_s: Five compartments shown commemorating the successes of Eugene and Marlborough during campaign of 1710.
issue_reverse_legend_s: MVNIMENTA OCCVPATA | DOVAY . | S . VENANT . | BETHVNE . | ARIEN . | MDCCX .
